/u/TrulyStupidNewb on Changing behaviors may be easier when people see norms changing - "In a study, people ate less meat and conserved more water when they thought those behaviors reflected how society is changing."
Someone already figured this out before the study. "Become the change you want to see in the world". It's the most peaceful, and one of the most effective ways to get others to change. I've given up my car for 16 years and I'm not even an environmentalist. You wouldn't believe how many environmentalists get self-defensive when I even suggest that giving up driving can be a viable option.   